15/01/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi visited Shkodra on Thursday (January 14th) saying the worst of flooding damage is over while praising the efforts of volunteers and other rescue workers. With Topi were European Commission head Helmut Lohan, US Ambassador John Withers and Spanish Ambassador Manuel Montobbio. 
Also Thursday, the Albanian Ministry of Work and Social Welfare said it will forward for government approval a decision to aid all families affected by the floods. Nearly 2,200 properties in Shkodra were damaged. (Lajmifundit, Top Channel, Klan - 14/01/10)

